The paper deals with compressed sensing signal reconstruction problems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of approximate message passing (AMP) and density estimation approaches also suggests a possible fit with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on universal denoising and ergodic signals could also make it relevant to the Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
